                  <additions>
                     <t:list xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#ir">-ir</locus>
                           <desc>Waqf</desc>
                           <q>وقف لله لاخ على مصطفى البار رحمه الله وكعل ناظره محمد أمين</q>
                           <note>Front leaf.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#3r">-3r</locus>
                           <desc>Title</desc>
                           <q>كتاب متن المنهج على اتمام الكمال  تاليف الشيخ الامام العالم العلامة العمدة الفهامة ولي الله بلا نزوع ابي يحيي زكريا الانصاري نسبا والشافعي مذهبا تغمده الله برحمته واسكنه فسيح جنتة بفضله وكرمه امين امين وصلى الله وسلم علي نبينا محمد واله وصحبه اجمعين</q>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#Throughout the text">-Throughout the text</locus>
                           <desc>Glosses</desc>
                           <q>Several lexicographic and analytic glosses, mentioning al-Birmāwī, al-Zayyādi and al-Baǧīramī as sources.</q>
                           <note>Glosses almost all by the same hand; some glosses are marked with one or more "ǧīm" at the end.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#172v">-172v</locus>
                           <desc>Fawā'id and masā'il</desc>
                           <q>Mas'ala about the unlawfulness for the master to vilify his disciples; fawā'id about Abū Ḥanīfa's and al-Ḥakīm al-Tirmiḏī's vision of God and about an invocation for forgiveness.</q>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#173v">-173v</locus>
                           <desc>Adʻiya and doxologies</desc>
                           <q>Invocations to be recited on Friday.</q>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#173r">-173r</locus>
                           <desc>Fawā'id and masā'il</desc>
                           <q>Fā'ida about the first memorizers of the Quran.</q>
                           <note>Pen trials written on part of page.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <locus target="#3r-4r">-3r-4r</locus>
                           <desc>Fawā'id and masā'il</desc>
                           <q>Different fawā'id about the number of God's Names (quoting al-Ḥakīm al-Tirmiḏī), letters to be written on a book to be able to answer every question, orthography, grammar and lexicography (mentioning al-Birmāwī), different categories of people (according to they degree of faith), seeing God in dream, position of Sun and Moon in the heavens, importance of the intention (niyya) to perform ritual prayer, a biography of al-Šāfi‘ī, spiritual meaning of the point under the bā' (mentioning al-Birmāwī), meaning of the prayer of different beings (mentioning al-Šanwānī), sexual intercourse before the woman performed the major ablution (ġusl) after menstrual period (mentioning al-Qarāfī and al-Birmāwī), lifespan of flies and the punishment of hell (mentioning Ibn al-Buḫārī's Tā'rīḫ and al-Birmāwī), spiritual degrees of praise, meaning of the word "dīn" (religion), definition of the status of ṣaḥābī according to the Šāfi‘ī maḏhab, nature and conditions of God's help,</q>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                     </t:list>
                  </additions>
